##Will patients with new coronary disease "relapse" ? The nucleic acid test of a few discharged patients was suspected to be false negative

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

The timing, duration and difficulty of seeing a doctor of these patients varied, but they still did not know whether they were "relapsing" or not cured? They had been counted as cured and discharged from the hospital, and the sudden onset of symptoms and retesting meant they were not actually cured

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Article | Caijing Reporter, Fang Gong Yi Liu Yi Qin, Ji Lu, Li Shiyun

Editor | Song Wei

Feb. 20,2020, a new pneumonia patient in Jinyuan community, Wangjiang, Chengdu, was discharged from the hospital after being declared cured. During isolation, he was rechecked for positive DNA test paper. This triggered alarm among the local population, who feared a "relapse" or "secondary infection" .

The patient's colleagues told Caijing that the unit did have the patient, but did not confirm whether he was hospitalized again, and that the patient had no contact with colleagues before or after the outbreak. A call was made to the hospital where the patient was, but no response was received.

On February 21, Lei Xuezhong, a member of the Expert Group on medical treatment of new coronary pneumonia in Sichuan Province, said that the number of cases of such cases being re-diagnosed after recovery from hospital was very small, and similar cases had been reported in China before. But this case is not a recurrence, more likely is a small number of virus persistence. But according to our reporter, this explanation is not the consensus of the medical profession.

Can such a patient be considered a true "cure" ? Should the discharged and readmitted patient be considered a "cured" case or a newly "confirmed" case, according to the statistical criteria for new crown pneumonia?

"It is against the basic principles of virology and immunology that the recovered person reinfects immediately, " the Li Ka Shing Faculty of Medicine told Caijing

Regarding "the persistence of a few viruses" , Professor Jin Dongyan thinks this is an unscientific argument. The most likely, he says, is a false negative caused by uncertainty. Under normal circumstances, the viral load will also have high or low changes, and viral load reduced, because of the sensitivity of detection reagents and sampling factors, may bring false negative. "It's the most direct way to admit this. Otherwise, it's against common sense to explain it with other strange reasons, " Jin said.

On February 21, the day after the Wangjiang Jinyuan case in Chengdu, China's National Health and Health Commission released the fifth edition of the COVID-19, nEGATIVE NUCLEIC ACID test results can not rule out COVID-19 infection, we need to rule out the possibility of producing false negative factors. This authoritative explanation is basically consistent with Professor Jin Dongyan's statement.

Zhao Jianping, head of the Hubei Expert Group, said that the positive rate of DNA test in nasopharyngeal swabs was only 30-40% . "If the number of false negative cases increases, it may further cause human-to-human transmission after discharge, " Shen Jun, assistant director of the Central South Hospital Emergency Center and director of Emergency Surgery, told CAIJING.

"CAIJING" reporters learned that Wuhan People's Hospital and a large hospital in Jiangxia District medical staff, have been discharged from the hospital isolation period nucleic acid positive re-admission. The first cured case was discharged from hospital in Jingzhou, Hubei Province on January 27. Recently, the patient developed symptoms again and was readmitted after testing positive for nucleic acid test paper.

The discharge criteria for the above patients, according to the fifth revised edition of the diagnosis and treatment plan for COVID-19 pneumonia issued on February 8, the criteria for release from isolation and hospitalization are: Body temperature returns to normal for more than 3 days, and respiratory symptoms improve significantly, negative for respiratory pathogens (at least 1 day interval between sampling) for two consecutive sessions.

On February 18, the program was revised to its sixth edition, with the addition of "pulmonary imaging showing significant improvement in acute exudative lesions" and "post-discharge precautions. ".

By 24:00 on February 22,2020,76,936 cases had been confirmed and 22,888 cases had been cured. As it stands, there are very few cases of patients being diagnosed after being discharged from the hospital, but medical experts caution that such cases also deserve attention because of the potential for transmission of the virus.

Through carding and re-disk, "CAIJING" reporters learned that this is more discharge standards, nucleic acid test paper accuracy and post-discharge isolation measures.

"In order to rule out infection, we should also test the antibody, if the antibody is more than four times higher, then we will enter the convalescence period. So I suggest to produce antibody reagent in quantity for auxiliary diagnosis, " said Professor Jin Dongyan.

Hospitals in cities outside Wuhan, including those in Huangshi, Jingzhou and Xiaogan, told Caijing that discharged patients could return for daily visits. But most hospitals in the city, including the Golden Pond Hospital in Wuhan, said it was difficult for hospitals to call back every day, patients need to self-observation, self-isolation.

Follow-up of patients discharged from hospitals in Wuhan is expected to be better addressed from February 23. On the evening of February 22, the new crown pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters in Wuhan issued a notice on the recovery and isolation of discharged patients with new crown pneumonia, discharge patients should go to the designated place to implement 14 days of free rehabilitation isolation and medical observation. At the end of the observation period, those who are physically fit will be released from quarantine. Outside Wuhan, the measure has not been followed up, with tens of thousands of infected people in hospitals across the country and more than 20,000 convalescent patients in self-isolation.

In some areas of Hubei, the epidemic is still climbing, from Hubei to the country, the epidemic prevention war is still continuing. With a large number of new pneumonia patients discharged from hospital, a new challenge has emerged: How to play more than 20,000 recovered patients follow-up defensive warfare.

Discharged and readmitted patients

On Feb. 12, Liu's father was discharged from a new pneumonia hospital in Wuhan and returned to the The Empty Family, where his mother had died of the disease.

Liu Yang told the CAIJING reporter that on February 10, the hospital according to the elderly did not appear more than 3 days of fever, cough symptoms, asked its discharge. In Liu Yang's strong request, the hospital for the elderly to do a nucleic acid test paper examination, but did not tell the results of the examination, the hospital still let the elderly discharge. On Feb. 12, Liu's family took his father home, out of trust in the doctors and an understanding of the shortage of beds. But the old man didn't get a CT when he left the hospital.

The 80-year-old man, isolated at home, rely on neighbors to send food to cook their own. A few days later, he developed fever again. On 18 February, the children returned him to the hospital where he had been hospitalized. The man's latest nucleic acid test came back positive for Florida.

Even if a few days later again in hospital, the family did not know when the discharge test results, hospital did not explicitly inform the family, the elderly is a recurrence or not yet cured?

Half a month, the old man lost his wife, himself in the hospital, transfer, discharge, home, again between the hospital toss and turn. "CAIJING" reporters asked the hospital's doctors, doctors said his department discharge, is strictly in accordance with the discharge standards, and did not know about other departments.

Around the same time, medical staff at another hospital told Caijing that the first confirmed patient in Jingzhou, and the first discharged patient in Jingzhou, had been readmitted.

"Wang walked out of the isolation ward holding flowers sent by medical staff, " said the patient, who worked as a porter at the south China Seafood Market in Wuhan, according to high-profile local media reports, he was referred to the outpatient department of the Chest Surgery Hospital of Jingzhou on 7 January. Before he was discharged, he tested negative for nucleic acid test twice in a row.

More recently, he was brought back under the radar and admitted to a hospital in Jingzhou that specializes in the treatment of the most severe cases.

The medical staff of the hospital told the reporter from Caijing that due to the protection of patient privacy, the hospital system has been unable to check the status of the patient's case recently, only knowing that the patient has been admitted, but not knowing the course of the disease, it was not clear whether the hospital had identified it as a secondary infection, a recurrence, or as yet uncured.

At the same time unknown, is in Wang discharge from the hospital within nearly two weeks of home quarantine period, there is no infectious family and entourage?

After all, families can not reach the isolation of a hospital. According to the sixth edition of the COVID-19, the mode of transmission of the virus is: "By respiratory droplets and close contact transmission is the main route of transmission. In a relatively closed environment, long-term exposure to high concentrations of aerosols through aerosol transmission is possible. " Therefore, isolated homes are not completely safe.

"Some cases have fever again after discharge from hospital or become the source of infection again, " Zhao Jianping, head of Wuhan Xinguan Medical Treatment Group, told the Beijing News on Feb. 18

These ordinary patients, after experiencing the discomfort of treatment, the relief of discharge from the hospital, and returned to the ward. They do not have a doctor's professional perspective, do not know the specific reasons for readmission, but also worried about contact after discharge from the family situation. A Jiangxia District volunteer told Caijing that a nurse close to him had been hospitalized again during a 14-day isolation period. "She's getting worse and she's very unstable. "

At the same time, as the case of Chengdu Wangjiang Jinyuan residential area, these cases although is an individual case, but has caused alarm and panic around the people.

A person close to the Wuhan People's Hospital told Caijing that the hospital has recently raised the discharge standards for medical staff and increased the number of nucleic acid tests from the required two to five.

Health care workers are particularly at risk because they need to be ready to go on duty immediately after the quarantine is lifted. At the same time, their resistance may be lower due to physical exertion.

The average patient, when they become symptomatic during discharge from the hospital, will go through the community-based clinic again, just like any other patient. Li Yang, who was discharged from a hospital in Wuhan about 10 days ago, said she developed fever on the eighth day of isolation and found her home in a community in Hankou. The community said she had to wait in line for a CT appointment, but the issue remained unresolved two days later.

On the evening of February 22, the community said that she had been placed in quarantine at the hotel, but that her family had not been placed in quarantine. The community then changed its tune and told her to go to the hospital the next day for a follow-up check and not to be quarantined for a while. At this point, Li Yang's temperature was 37.3 degrees.

The timing, duration and difficulty of seeing a doctor of these patients varied, but, in common, they still did not know whether they were "relapsing" or not cured. They were all convalescents counted in the cure statistics, and the sudden onset of symptoms and positive test results told them that they weren't really cured at all.

The Yin and Yang test paper

Dr. Liu Baohui of Wuhan People's Hospital told Caijing that re-admission cases exist, but confirmed cases can not be "confirmed. ".

Doctors and researchers are still learning more about the virus in the case of repeated hospitalizations.

The first thing that scientists and doctors think is less likely is secondary infection and recurrence. Virologist Jin Dongyan told "CAIJING" reporter: "The convalescent immediately reinfection, this is completely against virology and immunology basic principles. The human body relies on the immune response against the virus, the immune response after the encounter of the virus will be activated, not in a short period of time quickly subsided. No more infections for at least six months, a year."

Patients after treatment, through the national uniform standards after discharge, that is, as the statistical caliber of the cured discharged. CAIJING reporter obtained Jingzhou "new crown pneumonia discharge patients follow-up work program, " patient discharge data statistical flow is: Isolation area daily report ready to discharge patient information; next, outpatient confirmed and reported two days after the discharge of patients in advance information, to the city control command medical treatment group. The Rehabilitation Department will work out the rehabilitation recommendations for each patient before discharge.

"The criteria for discharge are reasonable and improving, and the nature will not change, " Liu said.

But beyond statistical caliber, is patient discharge a cure in the medical sense? For now, it seems, there are still a few standard and unexpected iterations.

Professor Jin Dongyan believes that such patients discharged after re-admission, the most likely cause is the nucleic acid test paper caused by false negative. Under normal circumstances, the viral load has high or low changes, and the viral load reduced, because the relationship between reagent sensitivity and sampling did not detect, it may bring false negative.

Shen Jun, a doctor at Wuhan University's Zhongnan Hospital, also said that when new coronary patients are discharged and readmitted, the main problem is the uncertainty of testing methods. The degree of skilled operation of nurses and the position of test paper May influence the judgment of test result.

On February 21, the COVID-19 released the fifth edition of its guidelines for laboratory testing, which clearly states that a negative nucleic acid test does not rule out COVID-19 infection, factors that may produce false negatives need to be ruled out.

At the same time, the discharge criteria of lung CT mostly depend on the experience of doctors. The criteria are: CT shows significant improvement in exudative lesions, but not complete absorption."

Because "substantial damage to the lungs can leave marks, like scars on the skin, " Shen Jun says, such as fibrosis in the lungs of patients with new pneumonia. Therefore, the doctor to the lung CT judgment may also have the omission.

Shen Jun said the best test might be to find out if an antigen like hepatitis B is present in a patient's body, but that knowledge of the virus is still expanding and such tests are not available.

Professor Jin Dongyan believes that in order to exclude infected patients, should be measured at the same time antibody, such as antibody has more than four times high is to enter the recovery period. So we should mass-produce antibody reagent as soon as possible to make auxiliary diagnosis.

A virus in the shadows and in the light

If there is no clinical feature of NCP, could it also be the "virus residue" of the medical treatment Expert Group of NCP in response to the case in Jinyuan District of Chengdu?

According to Wang Chen, a respiratory and critical care specialist and vice president of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, who spoke to the CCTV-13 on Feb. 19, the new pneumonia could turn into a chronic, flu like disease that persists in humans for a long time.

In this regard, Professor Jin Dongyan's point of view is that "the virus into chronic" and "virus residue" are not scientific enough. "unless the patient is immunocompromised, the likelihood is very low. "

"I personally think that patients who have built up immunity are not the ones we need to worry about. We need to focus on the so-called asymptomatic infectees, " Liu said. Asymptomatic infection, that is, without outside intervention, from the beginning to the end without symptoms but infected with the virus. Because there are no symptoms, they may not take the initiative to check.

According to a recent Japanese study, asymptomatic infections accounted for 40 percent of all infections among Japanese evacuees from Wuhan, while among the 126 Germans who left Hubei, according to a study of German evacuees, the researchers found two asymptomatic infections and two symptomatic infections, with asymptomatic infections accounting for 50 percent of all infections.

"although the sample size of this type of study is small, there may be bias, but at least it shows that the proportion of asymptomatic infection is much larger than previously known, " Liu said.

Recently, Wang Meiyun's team at the Henan Provincial People's Hospital reported on a patient in Anyang, Henan Province, who infected five family members during the asymptomatic period, showing that asymptomatic infected people can also infect others. And a paper published by researchers at the The New England Journal of Medicine, Guangdong CDC, National Sun Yat-sen University, and the University of Hong Kong also confirmed that the throat swab virus concentrations of asymptomatic infected people were no different from those of symptomatic infected people.

All this suggests that asymptomatic infections are likely to be equally contagious.

Liu Baohui said this could have three consequences: first, the virus would continue to spread and become less infectious, so that it could not infect others and the virus would disappear; Second, the virus would be contagious but would not cause illness to most people, it means that we may have a long-term coexistence with the virus; third, the recessive infection may cause disease again, causes the infection.

"these punctate outbreaks are not necessarily caused by discharged patients, but I personally think they are more dangerous, " he said.

In response, Liu Baohui suggested that it was imperative to study the time window for transmission of the virus. Current control measures in Wuhan can effectively prevent further transmission of asymptomatic infection, but can not cut off transmission within families.

Thus, current controls require at least two windows of infection to be in place in order to completely cut the transmission chain from asymptomatic infected individuals out of the home.

It also means that measures to isolate, diagnose and treat asymptomatic infections, recovered patients and suspected cases need to be improved if the epidemic is to be won.

On the evening of February 22, the following day after the re-admission of the case to the hospital in Jinyuan, Wangjiang, Chengdu, received widespread attention, the new Wuhan Pneumonia Prevention and Control Headquarters issued a notice on the recovery and isolation of discharged patients from the hospital after being cured of the disease. The notice said that from today, discharged patients should be designated places to implement a unified 14-day free rehabilitation isolation and medical observation. At the end of the observation period, those who are physically fit will be released from quarantine.

As of 2400 hours on February 22nd, Wuhan has 46,201 confirmed cases and 8,171 cured cases, which means that the post-discharge tracking and Defense Campaign for the thousands of discharged people is about to begin in depth.

Outside Wuhan, only in the rest of Hubei Province, as of 2400 hours on February 22, there were 10,265 confirmed cases still in hospital, how to implement the isolation conditions after discharge from hospital, whether the awareness of isolation education can be put in place, still needs to be strengthened. The small number of discharged cases that are not strictly equivalent to a cure is a reminder that the complexity of the new coronavirus remains to be further understood.

(intern Ma Kexin also contributed research. At the request of the interviewee, Liu Yang and Li Yang were pseudonyms.)
